The paper focuses on the writing of scientific papers and uses data from the arXiv e-print repository, which is a preprint server for computer science and other fields. The paper specifically mentions studying computer science and mathematics, which narrows down the potential sub-categories. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is likely because the paper discusses the use of LaTEX, a typesetting system commonly used in natural language processing. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are also likely because the paper discusses analyzing large amounts of scientific literature. cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are less likely but still possible because they are broad sub-categories that could potentially include research on analyzing scientific literature.
